        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 1<supplied reason="lost">5</supplied><ref n="1"
                                target="#Deut-015-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut015-P306r-L21_trl" n="21"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.014.trl.xml#Deut014-P306r-L21_trl" />
                        <l n="1">In the course of
                            <milestone unit="page" n="306v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             seven years you shall make a remission.</l>
                        <l n="2">And this is the matter of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             remission: every man is to release his debt of his hand that he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             lends to his fellow. He shall not press his fellow or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             his brother, because it is called the Lord’s release.</l>
                        <l n="3">A
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             foreigner you may press, but whatever of yours is with your brother you
                            shall release
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             the debt of your hand.</l>
                        <l n="4">Nonetheless, there will be no <supplied reason="lost"
                                >needy</supplied> among you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             because the Lord will surely bless you in the land which the Lord your
                            God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             gives you for a portion to inherit it —</l>
                        <l n="5">Only if
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             you listen to the voice of the Lord your God to keep and to do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             all these commandments which I command you today.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="6">Because the Lord your God blesses you, as he spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             to you, and you will give on pledge to many kingdoms, but you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             will not take one pledge. And you will reign over many kingdoms,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             but they will not reign over you.</l>
                        <l n="7">If there is a poor man among you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             from one of your brothers in one of your cities in your land that the
                            Lord your God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             is giving you, you shall not harden your heart and you shall not shut
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             your hand from your poor brother.</l>
                        <l n="8">Because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             you shall surely open your hand to him and shall surely give him on
                            pledge,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             sufficient for his shortage, in that which he lacks.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="9">Take heed to yourself, lest there will be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             a worthless word in your heart, saying, “The seventh year, the year of
                            <milestone unit="page" n="307r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             release, is getting close,” and your eye will look evilly against your
                            poor brother,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and you will not give him, and he will cry to the Lord against you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and it will be sin in you.</l>
                        <l n="10">You shall surely give
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             to him, and your heart shall not refuse to comply when you give to him:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             because for this thing the Lord your God will bless you in all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             your works and in all that you reach your hand out to.</l>
                        <l n="11">Because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the poor will never cease out of the land.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             On account of this I command you, saying, “You shall open
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             your hand to your brother, to your poor, and to your needy in your
                            land.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="12">And if your brother, a Hebrew man or a Hebrew woman, is sold to
                            you:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             and he shall serve you six years, and in the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             seventh year you shall let him go free from you.</l>
                        <l n="13">And when
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             you send him out free from you, you shall not send him empty.</l>
                        <l n="14">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             You shall present him some of your flock and of your threshing-floor
                            and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             of your winepress; as the Lord your God has blessed you, you shall give
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             him, too.</l>
                        <l n="15">And you shall remember that you were a slave in the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             of Egypt, and the Lord your God redeemed you. On account of this I
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             command you this word today.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="16">And it shall be, if he says to you, “I will not go away from you,”
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             because he loves you and your house, because it was good
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             for him with you,</l>
                        <l n="17">Then you shall take an awl and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="307v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             put it in his ear and in the door, and he shall be your servant
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             forever. And you shall also do this to your maidservant, <seg
                                type="commented" corresp="#Deut-015-seg001_trl" />because you shall
                            not send her empty,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             but you shall present her with that which your hand can attain<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Deut-015-seg001_trl" /><ref n="2"
                                target="#Deut-015-fn2_trl" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="18">It shall not seem hard in your eyes when you send
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             him away free from you, because he served you for a wages equal to two
                            wages of a hired servant
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             for six years, and the Lord your God will bless you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             in all the works of your servants that you will do.</l>
                        <l n="19">All the firstborn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             male that is born in your herd and in your flock
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             you shall keep holy to the Lord your God. You shall do no work
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             with the firstborn of your bull, and you shall not shear the firstborn
                            of your sheep.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="20">You shall eat it before the Lord your God, <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Deut-015-seg002_trl" />each man that which he is allowed
                            to eat,<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Deut-015-seg002_trl" /><ref
                                n="3" target="#Deut-015-fn3_trl" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             every year in the place which the Lord shall choose, you and your
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             household.</l>
                        <l n="21">And if there is any blemish in it — lame
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             or blind, any ill blemish — you shall not sacrifice
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             it to the Lord your God.</l>
                        <l n="22">You shall eat it within your cities,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the unclean and the clean person |shall eat it| alike, like the deer
                            and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             like the fawn.</l>
                        <l n="23">Only: you shall not eat its blood.
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut015-P307v-L18_trl" n="18"
                                next="ADub.III.73.005.016.trl.xml#Deut016-P307v-L18_trl" />
                             You shall pour it like water on the earth.</l>
                    </ab>
